<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745578>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–14. Species of Iteaphila with unbranched R 4+5. 11, I. beringiensis sp. nov., male, lateral view, scale bar = 1 mm; 12, I. bartaki sp. nov., male, lateral view, scale bar = 1 mm; 13, I. dichoptica sp. nov., male holotype, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 14, I. flavipilosa, female, dorsal view, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745578/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745586>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21–25. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R 4+5. 21, I. beringiensis sp. nov., lateral view; 22, I. bifida sp. nov., lateral view, with arrow indicating apex of phallus in posterior view; 23, I. recta sp. nov., lateral view; 24, I. tribulosa sp. nov., lateral view; 25, same, apex of hypandrium, posterior view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; epand— epandrium; epand brg—epandrial bridge; hypd—hypandrium; ph—phallus; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745586/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745600>
    dc:description "FIGURES 45–48. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R, lateral view. 45, I. gracilis sp. nov.; 46, I. grandis sp. 4+5 nov.; 47, I. lolo sp. nov.; 48, I. longipalpis (Melander). Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; epand brg—epandrial bridge; hyprct proc—hypoproct process; ph—phallus; ph gd—phallic guide; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745608>
    dc:description "FIGURES 53–57. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R 4+5. 53, I. luteitibia sp. nov., lateral view; 54, I. nupta (Melander), lateral view; 55, I. sierrensis sp. nov., lateral view; 56, I. spinosa sp. nov., lateral view; 57, same, left cercus, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; hypd—hypandrium; hyprct proc—hypoproct process; ph—phallus; ph gd—phallic guide; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745608/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745610>
    dc:description "FIGURES 58–61. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R, lateral view. 58, I. subnupta sp. nov.; 59, I. aktruensis 4+5 sp. nov.; 60, I. incus sp. nov.; 61, I. miranda sp. nov. Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: pgt—postgonite; ph—phallus; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745610/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745626>
    dc:description "FIGURES 75–78. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R 4+5. 75, I. zontaki (Nowicki), lateral view; 76, same, phallus, dorsal view; 77, I. parastentor sp. nov., lateral view; 78, I. stentor (Melander), lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: ph—phallus; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745626/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745590>
    dc:description "FIGURES 29–32. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R 4+5, lateral view. 29, I. bartaki sp. nov.; 30, I. falki sp. nov.; 31, I. kyrgyzstanensis sp. nov.; 32, I. ribesii (Becker). Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: cerc—cercus; ej apod—ejaculatory apodeme; goncx apod—gonocoxal apodeme; hypd—hypandrium; hyprct proc—hypoproct process; i apod—inner apodeme; ph—phallus; ph gd—phallic guide; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745590/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4745618>
    dc:description "FIGURES 66–70. Male terminalia of Iteaphila with unbranched R. 66, I. oedalina (Zetterstedt), posterior view; 67, same, 4+5 lateral view; 68, I. polygyna (Melander), lateral view; 69, I. recurvata sp. nov., lateral view; 70, I. sakhalinensis sp. nov., lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm. Abbreviations: pgt—postgonite; ph—phallus; sur—surstylus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4745618/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

